<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-24T23:18:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-24T23:18:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2800</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Siam</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-25T11:00:00+06:42">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 26, 11.14
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Replying circular telegram September 20, 6 p.m. Siamese Government,
                                sharing the United States Government’s friendliness towards Russia,
                                is in principle disposed to join United States and Allied powers in
                                the name of humanity in a protest against wanton destruction life
                                and liberty in Russia.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>